article.headline: Brown 63, Wagner 57
article.story: PROVIDENCE, R.I. (AP) -- Luke Ruscoe scored 15 points to lead Brown to a 63-57 win over Wagner on Tuesday night. After Brown (1-2) raced out to a 37-27 lead to start the second half, Wagner (0-2) rallied, outscoring Brown 17-6 over a 7-minute stretch to take a 44-41 lead with 9:44 to play. Nigel Wyatte scored 13 of his game-high 20 points during the Seahawks' run. Down 45-43 with 9 minutes to play, the Bears broke the game open by scoring 12 straight points, capped off by Jason Forte's 18-foot jumper with 5:31 remaining. Sean Munson scored 4 points in the next 29 seconds to pull the Seahawks within six points, at 55-49. Brown responded, as Patrick Powers hit a 3-pointer and Forte scored on a baseline jumper, giving the Bears a 60-49 lead with about 3 minutes remaining. In the first half, Brown broke a 17-17 tie with 7:17 to play, outscoring Wagner 14-5 during the remainder of the half and taking a 31-22 lead into halftime. Wyatte pulled down 20 rebounds and Munson added 11 points for Wagner.
